cellmate.accumulo.reader.celltransformer
Class AccumuloCellTransformers

Object
  AccumuloCellTransformers

public class AccumuloCellTransformers
extends Object

Static helper methods that offer concrete Cell transformers that cover a variety of common use cases for reading Accumulo Key/Value pairs into Cell groups.

The type-specific ValueQualToLabel methods set the cell label to the db qualifer, and the cell value to the db item value. Depending on which static method you call, you can optionally add ColumnFamily, and/or ColumnVisibility/Timestamp. The different typed versions are useful for automatically reading byte[] values directly to other primative types, but can produce undesirable behavior if the raw byte[] contents in the DB value were not persisted as the desired type.

For instance, a String written as a Key/Value pair to a byte[] might not appear properly when read back into a double[], even if the actual String could be cast as a double.

For this reason, most people will be interested in the String and byte[] versions of the ValueQualToLabel() transformer series. See SecurityByteCellTransformer and SecurityStringCellTransformer

A few additional transformer implementations are provided that collect all the records in a common bag, apply artifical labels on demand, and offer qualifier and total row aggregations.

public static CellTransformer<Map.Entry<Key,Value>,SecurityStringValueCell> stringValueQualToLabelWithTime_ColVis_ColFam()

The slightly different method names offer convinent ways to grab different combinations of the above settings, including different value types and exlusion/inclusion of column family, column visibility, and timestamp.

singleGroupByteValueCells

public static CellTransformer<Map.Entry<Key,Value>,SecurityByteValueCell> singleGroupByteValueCells()
Transformer that takes each incoming DB item and places in the same cell group. The DBReader will return one single Cell Group containing all the qualifiers and values see in the scan, regardless of which row key or column family they came from. Column family, column visibility, and timestamp are not written to the aux fields by this transformer.

Returns:
CellTransformer

colFamToCommonLabelOnMatches

public static CellTransformer<Map.Entry<Key,Value>,SecurityStringValueCell> colFamToCommonLabelOnMatches(Map<String,String> colFamToCommonLabel)
Transformer that takes a mapping of which column families get a constant label. Useful if your column family contains a group of qualifiers with no values, where the context for those qualifiers is simply their existance in the column family itself. If a Key/Value pair has a ColumnFamily not found in the map, transformer normally by the same logic found in the normal string value transformer. See also stringValueQualtoLabel()

Parameters:
colFamToCommonLabel - map of column families to apply common label.
Returns:
CellTransformer

averageSingleQual

public static CellTransformer<Map.Entry<Key,Value>,DoubleValueCell> averageSingleQual(String qual)
Aggregate transformer to read the Key/Value and for any matching the supplied qualifier, treat the Value byte[] as an integer. Return the average int value seen for all Key/Value containing the qualifier. null DBItem flag is sent by the Aggregate reader to signal end of scan iteration. This class works in conjunction with AggregateCellGroupingDBResultReader

Parameters:
qual - to calculate average int value.
Returns:
CellTransformer

aggregateSingleQual

public static CellTransformer<Map.Entry<Key,Value>,IntValueCell> aggregateSingleQual(String qual)
If reading Key/Values where the Value byte[] are integers, this transformer lets you get an aggregate sum of all the integer values that match a given qualifier. null DBItem flag is sent by the Aggregate reader to signal end of scan iteration. This class works in conjunction with AggregateCellGroupingDBResultReader

Parameters:
qual - to flag a Key/Value pair as an integer value and add to the sum.
Returns:
CellTransformer

aggregateMultiQual

public static CellTransformer<Map.Entry<Key,Value>,IntValueCell> aggregateMultiQual(String... qualifiers)
Same as aggregateSingleQual() but for multiple qualifiers. null DBItem flag is sent by the Aggregate reader to signal end of scan iteration. This class works in conjunction with AggregateCellGroupingDBResultReader

Parameters:
qualifiers - to flag a Key/Value pair as an integer value and add to the sum.
Returns:
CellTransformer

totalKeyValueCount

public static CellTransformer<Map.Entry<Key,Value>,IntValueCell> totalKeyValueCount()
Transformer that ignores the DB item contents and simply tallys how many discrete Key/Value pairs were seen by the scan. null DBItem flag is sent by the Aggregate reader to signal end of scan iteration. This class works in conjunction with AggregateCellGroupingDBResultReader

Returns:
CellTransformer
